[{"id":"VR914722","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a diagram of two incident electromagnetic waves, labeled Wave 1 and Wave 2, moving down onto the surface of oil that is floating on top of water. Wave 1 is perpendicular to the surface. Wave 2 is moving toward the surface at angle theta is greater than 0. A note states that the figure is not drawn to scale.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR914722.g01.svg\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">The figure shows two electromagnetic waves that are incident upon a thin, uniform layer of oil floating on top of water. Wave <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"1\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> has a wavelength <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"lambda sub 1\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"lambda sub 1\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>λ</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span> and is normally incident on the oil surface, while Wave <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"2\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> has an unspecified wavelength and an angle of incidence <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta is greater than 0\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"theta is greater than 0\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>θ</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math></span></span>. Each wave has a reflection at the air-oil interface as well as at the oil-water interface, and the oil film has the minimum thickness at which, for Wave <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"1\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span>, maximum constructive interference occurs between these two reflections. Which of the following claims about Wave <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"2\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> is correct?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR914722_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The two reflections of Wave <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> cannot interfere constructively for any wavelength value.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">If the two reflections of Wave <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> interfere constructively, its wavelength could be either longer than or shorter than <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"lambda sub 1\"><math alttext=\"lambda sub 1\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>λ</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span>.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">If Wave <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> has a wavelength of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"lambda sub 1\"><math alttext=\"lambda sub 1\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>λ</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span>, the two reflections of Wave <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> must interfere constructively.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The phase change due to transmission at the air-oil interface could be different for Wave <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> than for Wave <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span>.</p>"],"answer":1}]